# TypeScript & JavaScript Standards

When working with TypeScript or JavaScript in this project:

## General

- Prefer `const` over `let`; avoid `var`
- Use explicit types for function parameters and return values where helpful
- Prefer async/await over raw Promises

## Error Handling

```typescript
// BAD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {}

// GOOD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {
  logger.error("Failed to fetch", { error: e });
  throw new DataFetchError("Unable to retrieve data", { cause: e });
}
```

## Imports

- Use named exports when possible
- Group imports: external libs first, then internal modules
- Avoid circular dependencies
